    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for the discerning collector: a 2004 Porsche 911 (996.2) Carrera 4S in concours-level condition. This specimen features the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine, producing 320 hp with a broad torque curve thanks to VarioCam Plus valve timing. Power is managed by a G96 6-speed manual gearbox and sent to all four wheels via a viscous-clutch AWD system. Mechanical updates include a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a proactive cooling system overhaul. The wide-body chassis remains exceptionally rigid, supported by a factory-tuned suspension that exhibits no bushing deflection. Braking is handled by the iconic 'Big Red' monobloc calipers. This vehicle shows zero signs of bore scoring or oil consumption, maintaining peak compression across all cylinders. A true turn-key enthusiast example with a pristine undercarriage and original paint depth readings throughout.",
      "price": 48900.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
