    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a superlative 2011 Porsche 911 Carrera S, a mechanical benchmark featuring the 3.8L MA101 flat-six engine with Direct Fuel Injection (DFI). This unit is free of the IMS and bore-scoring concerns of earlier iterations, delivering a precise 385 hp through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), maintaining factory-spec damping rates and lateral rigidity. The braking system retains its original bite with zero glazing on the rotors, and the limited-slip differential provides flawless torque distribution. Meticulously preserved, the undercarriage shows no signs of heat-cycling fatigue or oxidation, and the paint depth is consistent across all panels, indicating a strictly garaged life. This is a turn-key, collector-grade specimen for the driver who prioritizes mechanical purity and documented service provenance.",
